The Estionia e-residency program have been launched since December 2014, I was lucky to learn about this program in 2019 when I just started my career in medical AI after completed my Ph.D. 

In the summer of 2021, I decided to set myself free from location dependent. Therefore I applied the e-residency and started a nomadic life. I have gone through the process of obtaining an e-residency. I went through the process of registering an Estonian business and opening a bank account as an e-resident. I've made mistakes, lost time and learned a lot in the past 1.5 years.

I will not go through the actual process of opening a business, because registering and managing a business in Estonia is quite straightforward if you choose a service provider like Xolo. They help to deal with regulations, accounting, and a mandatory business address. I started my company with Xolo and everything went really smoothly. 

I must confess that I changed to another provider this summer because of small issues such as Xolo accidentally charged me twice due to the bank was in some kind of updates. I manually paid the monthly fee but apparently Xolo makes the automatic charges every couple of days without checking whether the payment was already transferred. They of course reacted fast after I wrote to the customer service and refunded me. 

I am a person trusting my intuitions and in the summer I felt to change to another provider. Well, I felt the same for the banking but did not do it. It turned out sometimes you should be more rational. I switched to companio and even since regret about this decision. There are so much more manual work with companio, I lost some time each month for creating different documents. Xolo manages my business with more relaxation. 

Therefore I switched back to Xolo today (after three months because I found the additional work is a great burden). 

